1951;;Strictly Dishonorable;;American;;Melvin Frank;;Ezio Pinza, Janet Leigh;;rom com;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strictly_Dishonorable_(1951_film);;In New York in the 1920s, amorous opera star Augustino "Gus" Caraffa (Ezio Pinza) crosses paths with Isabelle Perry (Janet Leigh), a naive music student from Mississippi who is his biggest fan. When a news photographer catches them in a kiss, it is proposed that they get married in name only to avoid a scandal. Isabelle, who is in love with Gus, agrees to the charade, hoping that he will eventually fall in love with her.[2][3]